msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1941_10_glushkovo/date"
msgid "October 20th, 1941 - Glushkovo, north of Vyazma."
msgstr "20 de octubre de 1941 - Glushkovo, al norte de Viazma."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1941_10_glushkovo/name"
msgid "The Big Prize"
msgstr "Un gran premio"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1941_10_glushkovo/name_big"
msgid "The Big Prize"
msgstr "Un gran premio"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1941_10_glushkovo/narrator/officer/clearbridge"
msgid "Excellent! The bridge access seems to have been cleared."
msgstr "¡Perfecto! Ya tenemos acceso al puente."

msgctxt ""
"mission/single/02-ger/1941_10_glushkovo/narrator/officer/clearelevation"
msgid ""
"Excellent job soldiers. This elevated position will no longer be a threat "
"when the weather clears up."
msgstr "Bien hecho, soldados. Cuando el tiempo mejore, estar en las alturas ya no supondrá un problema."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1941_10_glushkovo/narrator/officer/clearford"
msgid ""
"Very good. It looks like the fording area has been cleared of hostile troops."
msgstr "Muy bien. Parece que en el vado ya no hay tropas hostiles."

msgctxt ""
"mission/single/02-ger/1941_10_glushkovo/narrator/officer/clearglushkovo"
msgid ""
"A fine display of tactical excellence, soldiers. The village has been "
"neutralized."
msgstr "Toda una lección de poder táctico, soldados. La aldea ha sido neutralizada."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1941_10_glushkovo/narrator/officer/glushkovo"
msgid ""
"Herr Leutnant, scouts are reporting tank movement towards the village of "
"Glushkovo. Unfortunately, in this weather, the Luftwaffe cannot help you."
msgstr "Herr Leutnant, nuestros exploradores nos informan de que varios tanques se dirigen a la aldea de Glushkovo. Por desgracia, con estas condiciones climatológicas, la Luftwaffe no puede apoyarte."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1941_10_glushkovo/narrator/officer/part2"
msgid ""
"Soldiers! We are not done yet! The enemy still holds the other river bank. "
"It is imperative we break through and seize all the strategic positions."
msgstr "¡Soldados! ¡No hemos terminado! El enemigo posee el lado opuesto al banco del río. Tenemos que irrumpir y capturar todas las posiciones estratégicas."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1941_10_glushkovo/narrator/officer/part2_2"
msgid ""
"Herr Leutnant, I have been told that we should expect the village of "
"Glushkovo to be heavily defended. The soviets are holding the line to "
"prevent encirclement of their troops between Vyazma and Bryansk."
msgstr "Herr Leutnant, me informan de que Glushkovo está muy protegida. Los soviéticos protegen la línea que rodea a sus tropas entre Viazma y Briansk."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1941_10_glushkovo/narrator/officer/reinf2"
msgid "Reserves and upgraded equipment are at your disposal Herr Leutnant."
msgstr "Herr Leutnant, dejo en tus manos reservas y equipamiento mejorado."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1941_10_glushkovo/narrator/officer/reinfshow"
msgid ""
"Reinforcements are at your disposal! Use them well. Our reserves are limited."
msgstr "¡Los refuerzos están a tu disposición! Úsalos con prudencia, no son ilimitados."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1941_10_glushkovo/narrator/officer/start"
msgid ""
"Soldiers! We have orders to clear the road for the attack on Vyazma. But the "
"village ahead keeps us from crossing the Dnieper, and is heavily defended."
msgstr "¡Soldados! Hemos recibido órdenes de despejar la carretera para invadir Viazma, pero la aldea de más adelante impide que podamos cruzar el Dniéper; está muy protegida."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1941_10_glushkovo/narrator/officer/start2"
msgid ""
"We must seize the Dnieper crossings and drive the enemy out of this sector! "
"I expect nothing but the very best from all of you! "
msgstr "¡Tenemos que hacernos con las travesías del Dniéper y expulsar al enemigo de este sector! ¡Espero lo mejor de vosotros! "

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1941_10_glushkovo/narrator/officer/tank_counter"
msgid "Soviet armored reserves are incoming from the east!"
msgstr "¡Se aproximan reservas blindadas rusas por el este!"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1941_10_glushkovo/narrator/soldier/nebelwerfer"
msgid ""
"Friendly casualties located! Those poor guys really ended up in the worst "
"possible place..."
msgstr "¡Bajas aliadas avistadas! Los pobres acabaron en el peor lugar posible..."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1941_10_glushkovo/outro_completed"
msgid ""
"After Glushkovo, the attack on Vyazma succeeded and the Germans marched "
"toward Moscow. However, because of the extreme cold \n"
"and a large scale Soviet counteroffensive, an attack on the Russian capital "
"was no longer on the cards. Little were they to know they would have to "
"fight over the same place just a few months later."
msgstr "Tras Glushkovo, el asalto a Viazma fue todo un éxito y los alemanes se encaminaron hacia Moscú. Sin embargo, por culpa del frío extremo \ny un contrataque soviético a gran escala, invadir la capital rusa ya no era una posibilidad. Ni se esperaban que unos meses después tendrían que luchar por el mismo lugar."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1941_10_glushkovo/outro_failed"
msgid ""
"Not crossing the Dnieper means not taking Vyazma, and many more casualties "
"for army group centre. This mission result means \n"
"the northern half of the attack on Vyazma is missing, delaying the end of "
"the encirclement by 4 weeks and stopping the German offensive when it "
"matters most."
msgstr "No cruzar el Dniéper significa no conquistar Viazma y sufrir más bajas por parte del Grupo de Ejércitos Centro. El resultado de la misión implica que \nha fallado la mitad norte del asalto a Viazma, retrasando así 4 semanas el fin del rodeo y deteniendo el asalto alemán cuando más potente era."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1941_10_glushkovo/place"
msgid "3rd Panzer Group, Army Group Centre."
msgstr "3.er Grupo Panzer, Grupo de Ejércitos Centro."

